Feature               | Spring Framework                                                                 | Spring Boot
----------------------|----------------------------------------------------------------------------------|---------------------------------------------------------------------------------

What is it?           | A massive, open-source framework used to build Java applications.                | An extension of Spring designed to make building applications faster and easier.

Primary Focus         | Provides core features like Dependency Injection (DI) and Inversion of Control.  | Focuses on rapid development and reducing configuration time.

Configuration         | Manual. Requires writing extensive configuration code (XML or Java configs).     | Automatic. Uses Auto-Configuration to detect and configure based on project files.

Server                | No built-in server. Must install and deploy to an external server (e.g., Tomcat).| Comes with an embedded server (e.g., Tomcat). Just run the app directly.

Dependencies          | Manually manage compatible versions in pom.xml.                                  | Provides Starter Dependencies (e.g., spring-boot-starter-web) that bundle everything automatically.

Boilerplate Code      | Requires repetitive setup/boilerplate code to get a basic app running.           | Eliminates boilerplate so you can focus on writing business logic immediately.

